revision.text:
'''Andrew Herman Apter''' (born December 7, 1956) is an American [[historian]], professor at [[University of California, Los Angeles]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.history.ucla.edu/people/faculty?lid%3D1337 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-05-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100613010345/http://www.history.ucla.edu/people/faculty?lid=1337 |archivedate=2010-06-13 |df= }}</ref> and Director of the African Studies Center.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.international.ucla.edu/person.asp?Facultystaff_ID%3D392 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-05-11 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110605231214/http://www.international.ucla.edu/person.asp?Facultystaff_ID=392 |archivedate=2011-06-05 |df= }}</ref>

He was field director of Black Atlantic Studies, for the [[Social Science Research Council]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ssrc.org/fellowships/subcompetitions/dpdf-fellowship/EC520470-3904-DD11-BEF0-001CC477EC70/2955EA66-475C-DE11-BD80-001CC477EC70/|title=Black Atlantic Studies - Dissertation Proposal Development Fellowship - Social Science Research Council (SSRC) - Brooklyn, NY, USA|website=Social Science Research Council|accessdate=11 August 2017}}</ref>

