{{unreferenced|date=March 2016}} {{Infobox book | name = Race Matters | image = Race Matters.jpg| caption = | author = [[Cornel West]] | country = United States | language = English | series = | subject = Race issues | genre = Social science | publisher = Vintage Books | pub_date = 1993 | pages = 159 | isbn = 0-679-74986-1 }}
'''''Race Matters''''' is a [[social sciences]] book by [[Cornel West]]. The book was first published on April 1, 1993 by [[Beacon Press]]. The book analyzes [[moral authority]] and racial debates concerning [[skin color]] in the United States. The book questions matters of economics and politics, as well as ethical issues and spirituality, and also addresses the crisis in black leadership.
